>
  <h2>Goal</h2>
  <p>
    Unified management of KVCache on DRAM/SSD, as an independent daemon, decoupled from inference frameworks (vLLM/sglang/MiniMax internal framework), while reporting KVCache metadata to scheduler for KVCache-aware scheduling.
  </p>

  <h2>Core Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Unified management of KVCache on DRAM + SSD</li>
    <li>Independent daemon, decoupled from inference frameworks</li>
    <li>KVCache metadata reporting to scheduler for KVCache-aware scheduling</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Architecture</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Independent Daemon</strong>: KVCache storage as independent component, not dependent on inference framework</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-tier Storage</strong>: Supports DRAM and SSD two-tier KVCache storage</li>
    <li><strong>Metadata Reporting</strong>: Reports KVCache metadata to scheduler</li>
    <li><strong>Framework Compatibility</strong>: vLLM, Sglang, MiniMax internal framework</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Results</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Saved thousands of GPUs</li>
    <li>Supports multiple inference frameworks</li>
    <li>Enables KVCache-aware scheduling</li>
  </ul>
</BlogLayout>
